import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['Wildlife_Species']]
    data = data.groupby(['Wildlife_Species']).size().reset_index(name='counts')
    data = data.sort_values(by=['counts'], ascending=False)
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.barplot(x="counts", y="Wildlife_Species", data=data, palette="Blues_d")
    ax.set(xlabel='Count', ylabel='Wildlife Species')
    ax.axvline(x=data['counts'].max(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Max Count: {:.2f}'.format(data['counts'].max()))
    ax.legend()
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.countplot(x="Aircraft_Make_Model", data=data, order=data['Aircraft_Make_Model'].value_counts().index)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90, horizontalalignment='right')
    chart.set_xlabel('Aircraft Make and Model')
    chart.set_ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of aircraft makes and models involved in incidents?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'])]
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Effect_Amount_of_damage', kde=True, color='green')
    plt.axvline(x=data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'].median()))
    plt.xlabel('Effect Amount of Damage')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the effect amount of damage caused by wildlife strikes?')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['Phase_of_flight'])
    chart = sns.countplot(x='Phase_of_flight', data=data, palette='Set2')
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    chart.axhline(y=data['Phase_of_flight'].value_counts().max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Max Count')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))

    plt.axvline(data['Cost_Total__'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f'Median: {data["Cost_Total__"].median():,.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('Total Cost of Incidents')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the total cost of incidents?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
